('18110', '1', 'This side dish would pair beautifully with roast lamb or salmon. To remove strings from fresh peas, just snap off the stem end and pull string lengthwise down each pod. Melt butter with oil in large nonstick skillet over medium heat.'),
('18110', '2', 'Add shallots and sauté until golden, about 5 minutes.'),
('18110', '3', 'Add sugar snap peas and radishes; sauté until crisp-tender, about 5 minutes.'),
('18110', '4', 'Add orange juice and dill seeds; stir 1 minute. Season with salt and pepper. Stir in chopped dill.'),
('18110', '5', 'Transfer to bowl; serve.'),
('18111', '1', 'Heat a large nonstick skillet over medium-high heat.'),
('18111', '2', 'Add pancetta, and saut 5 minutes or until crispy.'),
('18111', '3', 'Remove pancetta from pan, reserving drippings in pan.'),
('18111', '4', 'Add onion and garlic to pan; saut for 2 minutes or until tender.'),
('18111', '5', 'Add peas, broth, sugar, and salt to pan. Simmer 5 minutes or until the peas are tender, stirring occasionally. Stir in pancetta and chopped parsley.'),
('18116', '1', 'Prepare the orzo: Bring the broth to a boil in a medium saucepan.'),
('18116', '2', 'Add the orzo, reduce the heat, and simmer, uncovered, until just tender, 7 to 9 minutes.'),
('18116', '3', 'Drain, and return the orzo to the pan.'),
('18116', '4', 'Add the remaining ingredients and stir well to combine. Cover to keep warm.'),
('18118', '1', 'Bring water, onion, and 1/2 teaspoon salt to a boil in a heavy medium saucepan, then cook over medium heat, covered, stirring occasionally, until onion is tender, about 5 minutes.'),
('18118', '2', 'Increase heat to medium-high and stir in butter and peas, then cook, covered, stirring occasionally, until peas are tender, about 8 minutes. Season with salt.'),
('18131', '1', 'Combine first 6 ingredients in a small bowl.'),
('18131', '2', 'Heat a large nonstick skillet over medium-high heat; add orange juice mixture and snow peas. Cook 3 minutes, stirring often.'),
('18131', '3', 'Serve immediately.'),
('18134', '1', 'Cook shelled peas in large saucepan of boiling salted water until almost tender, about 1 1/2 minutes.'),
('18134', '2', 'Add sugar snap peas to same pan and continue boiling 30 seconds.'),
('18134', '3', 'Drain; rinse under cold water and drain again.'),
('18134', '4', 'Transfer to large bowl.'),
('18134', '5', 'Whisk vinegar, soy sauce, sesame oil, sugar, salt, and pepper in small bowl to blend. (Peas and dressing can be prepared 2 hours ahead.'),
('18134', '6', 'Let stand separately at room temperature.)'),
('18134', '7', 'Pour dressing over peas in large bowl; toss to coat. Season salad to taste with more salt and pepper, if desired.'),
('18134', '8', 'Serve at room temperature.'),
('18135', '1', 'Melt the butter in a large skillet over medium heat.'),
('18135', '2', 'Add the onion and cook 5 minutes.'),
('18135', '3', 'Add the sugar snap peas and cook, stirring occasionally, until bright green and crisp-tender, about 5 minutes.'),
('18135', '4', 'Mix in the sugar and salt and cook 1 minute more. Stir the half-and-half with 3 cups of water in a large measuring cup.'),
('18135', '5', 'Place half the snap-pea mixture in a blender or food processor.'),
('18135', '6', 'Pour in half the water mixture and puree until very smooth, 30 to 60 seconds. Repeat with the remaining ingredients.'),
('18135', '7', 'Pour the soup through a strainer and chill for at least 4 hours. Sprinkle with the chives (if desired) before serving.'),
('18139', '1', 'To prepare relish, combine first 8 ingredients in a bowl. Cover and chill.'),
('18139', '2', 'To prepare peas, sort and wash peas; set aside.'),
('18139', '3', 'Heat oil in a medium saucepan over medium-high heat.'),
('18139', '4', 'Add 1 cup onion and garlic to pan; saut 5 minutes. Stir in peas, broth, and remaining ingredients; bring to a boil. Cover, reduce heat, and simmer 20 minutes or until peas are tender. Discard bay leaf.'),
('18139', '5', 'Serve with relish.'),
('18144', '1', 'Heat a medium saucepan over medium-high heat. Coat pan with cooking spray.'),
('18144', '2', 'Add shallots to pan; saut for 1 minute or until tender.'),
('18144', '3', 'Add carrot; saut 1 minute. Stir in rice; saut 2 minutes.'),
('18144', '4', 'Add 1 1/2 cups hot water, thyme, and salt; bring to a boil. Cover, reduce heat, and simmer for 23 minutes or until rice is tender and liquid is absorbed.'),
('18144', '5', 'Remove from heat; stir in peas and Shrimp Butter.'),
('18144', '6', 'Let stand for 5 minutes or until peas are thoroughly heated and Shrimp Butter melts.'),
('18145', '1', 'Cut off and discard any skin from salt pork, then cut salt pork into 1/3-inch pieces. Cook in a 3-quart heavy saucepan over moderate heat, stirring occasionally, until most of fat is rendered and pork is golden and crisp, 6 to 8 minutes.'),
('18145', '2', 'Transfer pork with a slotted spoon to paper towels to drain.'),
('18145', '3', 'Pour off all but about 1 tablespoon fat from saucepan, then cook onion in fat over moderate heat, stirring, until softened, about 4 minutes.'),
('18145', '4', 'Add garlic and cook, stirring, 1 minute.'),
('18145', '5', 'Stir in peas and water and simmer, uncovered, until tender, 30 to 35 minutes. Stir in scallions and salt and pepper to taste.'),
('18145', '6', 'Serve peas over rice and sprinkle with salt pork.'),
('18147', '1', 'Place the pigeon peas in a small saucepan. Fill the pan halfway with water and rinse the peas by rubbing them between your fingertips. The water will become cloudy.'),
('18147', '2', 'Drain this water. Repeat three or four times, until the water remains relatively clear; drain. Now add 2 cups water and bring it to a boil, uncovered, over medium-high heat. Skim off and discard any foam that forms on the surface. Reduce the heat to medium-low, cover the pan, and simmer, stirring occasionally, until the peas are tender, about 20 minutes.'),
('18147', '3', 'While the pigeon peas are cooking, pour 4 cups water into a medium-size saucepan. If you are using the ball of tamarind, add it to the water and allow it to soften, 15 to 20 minutes. Then, using your fingers, break it apart and coax the pulp to leach and dissolve into the water as you massage the pieces. Once the water is light chocolate-brown and tastes tart, strain it through a fine-mesh strainer to separate out the pulp and any fibers; discard the pulp and fibers. Reserve the tamarind-infused water. If you are using tamarind paste, simply whisk it into the water to dissolve it.'),
('18147', '4', 'Sprinkle the Sambhar masala and asafetida over the tamarind water.'),
('18147', '5', 'Add the cauliflower, pumpkin, drumsticks, and curry leaves.'),
('18147', '6', 'Heat to a boil. Then reduce the heat to medium and simmer the thin brothlike curry, uncovered, stirring occasionally, until the vegetables are fork-tender, 15 to 20 minutes.'),
('18147', '7', 'When the pigeon peas are tender, set the saucepan aside.'),
('18147', '8', 'Heat 1 tablespoon of the oil in a small skillet over medium-high heat.'),
('18147', '9', 'Add the cashews, coriander seeds, and chiles, and stir-fry until the nuts and seeds turn reddish brown and the chiles blacken, 1 to 2 minutes. Scrape the skillets contents into a blender jar, and add  cup water and the coconut. Puree, scraping the inside of the jar as needed, to form a slightly gritty paste.'),
('18147', '10', 'Add this paste to the pumpkin mixture.'),
('18147', '11', 'Pour  cup water into the blender jar, swish it around to wash the jar out, and add this to the pumpkin mixture.'),
('18147', '12', 'Heat the remaining 1 tablespoon oil in the same skillet over medium-high heat.'),
('18147', '13', 'Add the mustard seeds, cover the skillet, and cook until the seeds have stopped popping (not unlike popcorn), about 30 seconds.'),
('18147', '14', 'Add this spiced oil to the pumpkin mixture.'),
('18147', '15', 'Transfer the cooked pigeon peas, with their cooking water, to a blender and puree, scraping the inside of the jar as needed, until smooth. (If you have an immersion blender, you can puree the peas and water right in the saucepan.)'),
('18147', '16', 'Pour this thin, creamy-yellow broth into the pumpkin mixture, and add the salt. Bring to a boil and then reduce the heat. Simmer, uncovered, stirring occasionally, until the flavors blend, about 5 minutes. Then serve.'),
('18147', '17', 'var article'),
('18147', '18', 'Type_27_data = {};'),
