('18158', '1', 'Cook the rice according to the package directions. Meanwhile, in a large bowl, combine the chicken, scallions, and ginger. Shape into 16 meatballs.'),
('18158', '2', 'Heat 1 tablespoon of the oil in a skillet over medium-high heat. Cook the meatballs, turning, until cooked through, 10 to 12 minutes.'),
('18158', '3', 'Transfer to a plate. Wipe out the skillet.'),
('18158', '4', 'Heat the remaining oil over medium-high heat.'),
('18158', '5', 'Add the peas and edamame. Cook, tossing, for 2 minutes. Return the meatballs to skillet. In a small bowl, combine the soy sauce and sugar.'),
('18158', '6', 'Add to the skillet and simmer until slightly thickened, 2 to 3 minutes.'),
('18158', '7', 'Serve over the rice. Tip: To keep the ground chicken from sticking to your fingers, wet your hands before forming the meatballs.'),
('18163', '1', 'Cook noodles according to package directions, then drain in a colander.'),
('18163', '2', 'Stir together oyster sauce, soy sauce, sugar, cornstarch, and water until smooth.'),
('18163', '3', 'Heat 1 tablespoon oil in a 10-inch nonstick skillet over medium-high heat until hot.'),
('18163', '4', 'Add noodles to skillet, pressing them with a rubber spatula to form a cake, and cook until underside is golden, 2 to 3 minutes. Flip cake over and drizzle 1 tablespoon oil around sides of cake, then cook until underside is golden, 2 to 3 minutes.'),
('18163', '5', 'Transfer noodle cake to a cutting board and cut into quarters.'),
('18163', '6', 'Heat 1/2 tablespoon oil in a wok or 12-inch heavy skillet over medium-high heat until it begins to smoke. Stir-fry snow peas with a pinch of salt until bright green, 1 to 2 minutes, then transfer to a plate.'),
('18163', '7', 'Add 2 tablespoons oil to wok and stir-fry scallions and ginger with 1/4 teaspoon salt 30 seconds.'),
('18163', '8', 'Add half of beef and cook, undisturbed, 45 seconds, then stir-fry until beef is just browned, 1 to 2 minutes more.'),
('18163', '9', 'Transfer to plate with snow peas.'),
('18163', '10', 'Add remaining tablespoon oil and cook remaining beef in same manner.'),
('18163', '11', 'Stir sauce mixture again, then add to wok and bring to a boil. Stir in beef and snow peas, then serve spooned on top of noodle cake.'),
('18166', '1', 'Fill a large saucepan with 1 inch of water and fit with a steamer basket (or fill a large skillet with 1/2 inch of water). Bring the water to a boil.'),
('18166', '2', 'Place the pot stickers in the basket (or skillet), cover, and steam for 4 minutes.'),
('18166', '3', 'Add the snap peas and carrots, cover, and steam until the pot stickers are cooked through and the vegetables are tender, 4 to 6 minutes. Meanwhile, in a small bowl, combine the soy sauce and sesame oil. Divide the bean sprouts among bowls and top with the pot stickers and vegetables. Sprinkle with the peanuts and scallions.'),
('18166', '4', 'Serve with the sauce.'),
('18168', '1', 'In a small bowl, whisk together the peanut butter, soy sauce, lime juice, broth, sugar, and coconut milk.'),
('18168', '2', 'Cut the chicken into 1-inch-wide strips.'),
('18168', '3', 'Heat the oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat.'),
('18168', '4', 'Add the chicken, chili, ginger, and garlic. Cook, stirring occasionally, until the chicken is golden, about 5 minutes.'),
('18168', '5', 'Add the snow peas and broccoli and cook until the vegetables are just tender, about 1 minute.'),
('18168', '6', 'Add the peanut sauce and cook until the mixture has thickened slightly and the chicken has cooked through, about 3 minutes.'),
('18168', '7', 'Garnish with the cilantro.'),
('18168', '8', 'Serve over cooked rice, if desired.Tip: You can easily substitute beef or shrimp for the chicken in this recipe. For beef, follow the same directions. For shrimp, cook all the vegetables, then add the shrimp, cook for 1 minute or until pink, add the peanut sauce, and finish the recipe from there.'),
('18169', '1', 'Place the olive oil, shallots, celery, and prosciutto in a 12 to 14-inch, deep-sided frying pan, and place over medium heat. Cook until soft but not brown, about 8 to 10 minutes.'),
('18169', '2', 'Add the rice and stir over medium heat for 2 minutes, until rice becomes almost opaque.'),
('18169', '3', 'Add the chicken stock to cover rice and turn heat up to high. As level of stock dips below level of rice, continue to add stock, 1 ladle at a time, to keep rice covered. Stir the rice constantly during this procedure.'),
('18169', '4', 'Taste the rice after 15 minutes: it should still be hard.'),
('18169', '5', 'Add the peas and continue cooking, until the rice is soft and creamy yet still "al dente". Rice should still be quite wet, but not swimming.'),
('18169', '6', 'Remove from heat and stir in butter and cheese. Adjust for seasoning and serve immediately.'),
('18169', '7', 'In a large, heavy-bottomed saucepan, heat the oil over high heat until smoking.'),
('18169', '8', 'Add all the chicken parts and brown all over, stirring to avoid burning.'),
('18169', '9', 'Remove the chicken and reserve.'),
('18169', '10', 'Add the carrots, onions, and celery to the pot and cook until soft and browned. Return the chicken to the pot and add 6 quarts of water, the tomato paste, peppercorns, and parsley. Stir with a wooden spoon to dislodge the browned chicken and vegetables bits from the bottom of the pan. Bring almost to a boil, then reduce heat and cook at a low simmer until reduced by half, about 2 hours, occasionally skimming excess fat.'),
('18169', '11', 'Remove from heat, strain, and press on the solids with the bottom of a ladle to extract out all liquids. Stir the stock to facilitate cooling and set aside. Refrigerate stock in small containers for up to a week or freeze for up to a month.'),
('18171', '1', 'Watch how to make this recipe.'),
('18171', '2', 'Bring a large pot of salted water to a boil over medium heat.'),
('18171', '3', 'Add pasta and cook until al dente.'),
('18171', '4', 'Drain pasta, reserving 1 cup of pasta water.'),
('18171', '5', 'Meanwhile, saute pancetta in a large saucepan over medium-high heat until golden and crisp, about 6 minutes.'),
('18171', '6', 'Transfer to a paper towel-lined plate. In the same pan, saute onions until softened, about 5 minutes.'),
('18171', '7', 'Add peas and garlic and saute for 3 minutes. Stir in Parmesan, pasta and pancetta. Moisten pasta with some of the reserved pasta water. Toss to incorporate, season with salt and pepper, if necessary, and serve, sprinkled with lemon juice.'),
('18172', '1', 'Brown the bacon in a skillet over medium heat until crispy; drain, crumble, and set aside.'),
('18172', '2', 'In a large saucepan, combine the canned black-eyed peas, canned tomatoes, onion, celery, garlic,  and jalapeno peppers. Cook over medium heat until the celery and onion are tender. Season with salt and pepper to taste.'),
('18172', '3', 'Add crumbled bacon before serving.'),
('18178', '1', 'Bring water to a boil in a medium saucepan.'),
('18178', '2', 'Add rice, 1 teaspoon oil, and salt; cover, reduce heat, and simmer 20 minutes or until liquid is absorbed.'),
('18178', '3', 'Heat 1 tablespoon oil in a large nonstick skillet over medium heat.'),
('18178', '4', 'Add onion, bacon, and garlic; cook 10 minutes or until lightly browned, stirring occasionally. Stir in rice, chopped green onions, cumin, pepper, and peas; cook 8 minutes or until thoroughly heated. Stir in parsley.'),
('18178', '5', 'Garnish with green onions, if desired.'),
('18182', '1', 'If using freshly shelled peas, cook in a 4- to 5-quart saucepan of boiling water (not salted), uncovered, until tender, 3 to 5 minutes, then drain in a colander.'),
('18182', '2', 'Briskly simmer cream with 1/4 cup mint in a 1- to 1 1/2-quart heavy saucepan until slightly thickened and reduced to about 1/2 cup, 4 to 5 minutes.'),
('18182', '3', 'Pour through a fine-mesh sieve into a bowl, pressing on and discarding mint.'),
('18182', '4', 'Cook celery and onion in butter in 4- to 5-quart heavy saucepan over moderate heat, stirring, until softened, about 4 minutes.'),
